`right()` methods. When navigating down, we store which side the child is
on relative to the parent. The original code incorrectly stored `'right'`
when going left, and `'left'` when going right. This caused `up()` and 
`toTree()` to reconstruct the tree with swapped children, breaking all 
navigation and mutation tests.

